VISHNU, One of the Trinity in Hindu Mythology is considered as the “Savior”. He is believed to dwell in deepest of Ocean called “vaikuntam".

He is believed to be in the “Anantasayana (Sleeping Pose) on the great Serpent” Adhishesha" (Serpent with 5 heads) and Adhishesha spreads his hood. Adhishesha is devotee of Vishnu and also accompanies Vishnu in his numerous avatars (incarnations). 

Vishnu is the Supreme god of the Vaishnavites (Hindu Religion) and many of the Vishnu’s avatars are encrypted in the advaithas.